(18, 13, '131622737237', '[{"blog_name":"instagram","id":131622737237,"post_url":"http:\\/\\/blog.instagram.com\\/post\\/131622737237\\/151021-tessyking","slug":"151021-tessyking","type":"photo","date":"2015-10-21 15:10:21 GMT","timestamp":1445440221,"state":"published","format":"markdown","reblog_key":"uY4YkNjT","tags":["photography","ceramic","enameling","art","Tessy King","instagram"],"short_url":"http:\\/\\/tmblr.co\\/ZMPd3x1wbKvLL","recommended_source":null,"recommended_color":null,"followed":true,"highlighted":[],"liked":false,"note_count":210,"caption":"<h1><strong>@tessyking\\u2019s Playful Art is a Labor of Love<\\/strong><\\/h1>\\n\\n<p class=\\"intro\\"><i>For more photos of Tessy\\u2019s art and her process, follow @<a href=\\"http:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/tessyking\\" target=\\"_blank\\">tessyking<\\/a> on Instagram.<\\/i><\\/p>\\n\\n<p>Though simple in form, Tessy King\\u2019s (@<a href=\\"http:\\/\\/instagram.com\\/tessyking\\" target=\\"_blank\\">tessyking<\\/a>) objects are laborious to create. For her enamel pieces she draws a shape onto a flat sheet of copper, cuts it out, cleans it and finally sprinkles enamel from a sieve onto the metal before firing it in the kiln. Then she repeats the enameling process in multiple layers until the colors look just right. The final product is often a brightly colored combination of basic shapes. \\u201cI see my objects as playful things that you can place in a space and rearrange,\\u201d says the Melbourne, Australia-based artist, whose work also includes ceramics. \\u201cMy grandfather was a carpenter, so growing up I was surrounded by wooden toys, like colored blocks and puzzles that when pieced together created a three-dimensional object.\\u201d Despite the process, for Tessy it\\u2019s a labor of love. \\u201cWith enameling you see the colors change each time,\\u201d she says. \\u201cI get absorbed in watching them evolve from start to finish.\\u201d<\\/p>","reblog":{"tree_html":"","comment":"<p><h1><strong>@t